<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,923,1136]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,923,949]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A monotypic genus of Nemophini with dorsal-fin spine pterygiophores that broadly contact robust vertebral neural spines (
<figureCitation box="[432,543,961,987]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2" captionStart-1="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1534,1557]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1606,1629]" captionTargetBox-0="[188,1398,1111,1512]" captionTargetBox-1="[163,1424,590,1565]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[188,1398,1111,1512]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,569,1582]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2. Partial radiograph of Adelotremus leptus, holotype. Digital radiograph by Sandra J. Raredon." captionText-1="FIGURE 3. Precaudal vertebrae 7 – 11 (epineurals and pleural ribs not shown) and associated pterygiophores, traced from digital radiographs, in two nemophin species: (A) Adelotremus leptus, holotype and (B) Petroscirtes thepassi, USNM 205296, male, 51.3 mm SL." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/213222/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/213223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
Figs. 
<number box="[498,543,961,987]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
</figureCitation>
A); absence of bi-pored lateral-line tubes; simple cirrus associated only with anterior 
<number box="[249,264,998,1024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
or 
<number box="[303,317,998,1024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
dentary sensory canal pores; 
<number box="[665,694,998,1024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" value="32.0">32</number>
total vertebrae; and only 
<number box="[994,1009,998,1024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" value="3.0">3</number>
infraorbital bones.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
