<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,923,1136]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,340,1072,1098]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[348,495,1073,1098]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Blenniidae" genus="Adelotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[348,495,1073,1098]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Adelotremus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a combination of the Greek 
<emphasis box="[862,938,1073,1098]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">adelos</emphasis>
(concealed) and 
<emphasis box="[1142,1209,1073,1098]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">trema</emphasis>
(hole), and alludes to the discovery of this fish hiding in a calcareous polychaete tube; gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
